observations.recommendation:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant and GSO to maintain complete property ledger cards and property cards, respectively, for all PPE owned by the agency;

Direct the GSO to provide the property number of all LGU properties and update the PAR; and

Direct the Municipal Administrator to submit the list of properties that must be insured with GSIS.

Require all Department Heads to show in the PPMP all items including a detailed list of goods and infrastructure projects to be procured during the year;

Require Department heads to submit to the BAC Secretariat their individual PPMPs which shall be evaluated and reviewed by the Municipal Budget Office and duly consolidated by the BAC Secretariat into an Annual Procurement Plan to support the appropriated amount in the approved Annual Budget; and

Direct the BAC Secretariat to consolidate the PPMPs into APP and to submit the report independent of the annual budget of the Municipality.

Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit the required interim financial statements, quarterly reports on unliquidated cash advances and quarterly report on the status of fund transfer on its prescribed period;

Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to submit quarterly a Status of Appropriations, Allotments, and Obligations (SAOB); and

Advise the Local Chief Executive to direct the MPDO or Municipal Engineering Office to ensure that the Audit Team Leader (ATL) is informed within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/activity that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted. Also, require the Municipal Engineer to submit the monthly as well as the quarterly report on projects.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit the required copies of PPE Local Road Network Ledger Cards (Annex D format) of COA Circular No. 2015-008; update the yearly required disclosures as needed; keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and prepare a lapsing schedule regularly for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year;
Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to maintain and submit Local Road Inventory and Road Maps; and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Cards for all roads and its components and submit the same to the Audit Team (Annex E format) of COA Circular No. 2015-008; and
Direct the Inventory Committee to submit Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network System (RPCLRN) supported with Local Road Network Maps (Annex C format) of COA Circular No. 2015-008.

Direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting entries to recognize the Trust Liability – DRRMF representing the unexpended funds; 

Ensure strict adherence to the prescribed accounts in recording LDRRMF transactions, specifically the use of Transfers of Unspent Current Year DRRM Funds;

Prepare the disclosures of LDRRMF in the notes to financial statement using the prescribed format.

Adhere strictly to the rates and conditions allowed under Section 4 of Annex D on advance payment;


Direct the BAC to comply with the sending of invitations to observers and to attach the same documents in the contracts;

Instruct the BAC to prepare and submit to the Municipal Accountant a BAC Resolution for procurements made under shopping or an excerpt of the APP indicating the items procured and that the method of procurement is an alternative method supporting the disbursements.

Create an inventory committee; prepare a timetable for the conduct of physical inventory; direct all Department Heads to coordinate with the Inventory Committee for cohesive planning;

