Instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit the 2022 bank reconciliation statements and ensure the timely submission of reports;

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit the CY 2022 bank statements, subsidiary ledger and photocopy of the cash in bank cashbook; and

Consider the augmentation of personnel assigned at the Accounting Office to prepare/assist in preparing the BRS.

Direct the TWG and BAC to be meticulous in the evaluation/ review of documents and reports;

Instruct the BAC Secretariat to comply with all the lacking documents; and

Require the BAC, Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant to explain in writing the deficiencies noted for each contract.

Direct the Municipal Engineer to prepare the Statement of Work Accomplished every month for every infrastructure project implemented by administration;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit the following documents for each project: 

Inspection Report by the Agency’s Authorized Engineer; 
Results of Test Analysis, if applicable;
Statement of Time Elapsed; 
Pictures, before, during and after construction of items of work especially the embedded items; 
Photocopy of vouchers of all previous payments; 
Certificate of Completion; 
Site development plan; 
profile sheet, typical section and details; drainage details where applicable;
structural plans at an appropriate scale indicating all details necessary in order that the complete structure can be set out and constructed.

Require the Municipal Assessor to prioritize the registration and transfer of title of the land to ensure ownership by the Municipal Government;




Require the Municipal  Budget Officer to provide budget for titling and other necessary expenses; and


Municipal Accountant to ensure land should be properly recorded in the books of accounts and secure deed of donations or deed of sale as basis in the titling and in the recording.

We recommended and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive:
Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit SB Resolutions and Certified List of affected families/persons noted by the MSWD and MDRRMO;
Require the Municipal Accountant to ensure the use of appropriate account names in the preparation of entries.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
Create an inventory committee; prepare a timetable for the conduct of physical inventory; direct all Department Heads to coordinate with the Inventory Committee for a cohesive planning;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant and General Services Officer to maintain complete property ledger cards and property cards, respectively, for all PPE owned by the agency;
Direct the General Services Officer to provide property number of all properties and update the PAR; and
Direct the Municipal Administrator to submit the list of properties that need to be insured with GSIS.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correct the financial statements and to transfer only the unexpended/unobligated balance of the QRF and the DRRMF-MOOE at the end of the year in the Trust Fund books;
Instruct the MDRRMO and Municipal Budget Officer not to include environmental activities to provide sufficient funds for the LDRRM programs.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Direct the Municipal Council for the Protection of Children (MCPC)  to ensure that programs, projects and activities are responsive to the needs of the children and to those identified in the Local Development Plan for Children (LDPC);
Instruct the Municipal Social Welfare and Development Officer and Municipal Budget Officer not to include Capacity building to Child Development Workers in the preparation of the budget and other similar activities that does not directly benefit the children.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Direct the Local School Board to prepare and submit Annual SEF Budget in the prescribed form and timeline pursuant to the new Joint Circular Dep Ed-DBM and DILG No. 1 s. 2017;
Instruct the Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Accountant to closely monitor the expenditures being charged against SEF.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Require the GAD Focal Person to submit a fully accomplished GPB that conforms to the required format of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No 2016-01;
Direct the GAD Focal Person to conduct gender mainstreaming, gender analysis/gender assessment and establish sex-disaggregated data information to identify the appropriate activities responsive to the needs of the LGU constituents and to require the prudent utilization of GAD fund and to limit its expenditures to GAD related activities only.

